The paper discusses wireless network security and device identification using fingerprinting techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses machine learning algorithms for fingerprinting, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses open research problems in the area of device fingerprinting, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of transmitted signals, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
